prd.overview:
PRD text fields today are plain strings: <overview>, <description>, the body of <rule> / <bug> children, and <finding> text are rendered verbatim in the dashboard and passed verbatim to Claude via the prd skill. This makes it awkward to:


call out emphasis in a long rule;

paste a screenshot of a failing UI into a bug;

share a code snippet that explains a rule;

point one PRD at another, the way dashboard/viewer already does for shared launch behavior.

This feature lets those fields contain inline XHTML so authors can format prose, embed images, and cross-link PRDs — while keeping the surrounding XML schema, the prd CLI, and the skill loader unchanged for callers that don't opt in.

requirement.rule:
An <a href="prd:<module>/<feature>"> link points to another PRD. Optionally a fragment selects a sub-element:


prd:<module>/<feature>#R3 — a requirement;

prd:<module>/<feature>#R3.rule_id — a specific rule;

prd:<module>/<feature>#bug.<bug_id> — a specific bug.
